1 This is one of the few films where I consider the film rendition to be an improvement on the original book . The story is clear , accessible , amusing and interesting and the musical numbers are without a doubt exceptional . I adored the cyclical rendition of ' The old home guard ' and the charming ' Portobello Road ' , a great combination of early animation + real actors techniques which , though dated do not detract from the charm of the piece . The background of the Second World War worked well and was not omitted as the film got under way , which so often happens in ' evacuee ' stories.<br /><br />An often far too underrated film , it produces no end to enjoyment for people of all ages . The performances from the actors are exceptionally well done and the entire text is neatly tied together and well designed . Guaranteed to put a smile on your face !
